result.execSummary:
The defendant Kayla L Jones was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Kayla L Jones is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Kayla L Jones was found guilty of Possession of THC (2nd+ Offense), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
9:49 a.m.  Defendant present in court without counsel.  Andrew Christenson for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant confirms receipt of the criminal complaint and waives reading. Court instructs the defendant of the maximum penalty on each count.  Court finds probable cause.  Court instructs defendant of her right to an attorney.  Court notes that bond has been set - $500 signature bond.  Court instructs defendant regarding her right to a preliminary hearing.  Defendant waives the time limits.  Court will set for Status of Counsel in approx 2-3 weeks.

Statement by defendant.  Court goes over right to counsel.  Defendant waives right to counsel.  Court accepts waiver.  Court instructs the defendant regarding her right to a preliminary examination.  Defendant waives her right to a preliminary examination.  Court accepts the waiver of the prelim and binds the defendant over for trial.  State files an information with the court.  Defendant acknowledges receipt of the information and waives any reading.  Defendant enters a plea of NO CONTEST.  DA recites offer, upon plea to count 1, will dismiss the place enhancer and count 2 and request a fine and costs.  

Court goes over constitutional rights with the defendant - defendant waives these rights.  Court goes over the elements of each offense.  Court instructs defendant of the maximum penalty.  Court instructs defendant regarding deportation.  Court instructs regarding felony prohibitions.  Defendant enters a plea of NO CONTEST to count 1.  Court finds the plea is made freely, voluntarily, intelligently and understandingly.  Court finds there is a factual basis to support the plea.  Court finds the defendant guilty to count 1.  Court strikes the place enhancer and dismisses count 2.  Court orders the judgment of conviction be entered here today.  Sentencing statement by DA.  No statement by the defendant.

Court sentences the defendant to:

$200 fine plus costs.  Court grants the defendant 60 days to pay or payment plan.

Court adjourned at 10:00 a.m.

1:07 p.m.  Defendant present in custody and via video from the Green Lake County Jail.  Lisa Vanden Branden for the State of Wisconsin.  Court finds probable cause.  Defendant confirms receipt of the criminal complaint.  Court goes over right to a preliminary hearing,  Court questions defendant regarding address and employment.  ADA makes bond recommendation.  Court orders a $500.00 signature bond.  Court goes over the right to a preliminary hearing.  Defendant will waive the time limits.  Court instructs the defendant to contact an attorney or the Public defenders office.  Defendant to appear for the Initial Appearance is on September 15, 2014 at 9:30 a.m.  Court goes over right to counsel.

Court adjourned at 1:13 p.m.
